estrictions. Now I'm distinguishing between compile-time warnings versus errors and runtime failures. The first two would trigger obsolete attribute warnings, the third creates an ambiguity error at compile time, and the fourth likely manifests as a runtime exception when the code actually executes, though it might also have an obsolete warning attached.","outputTokens":2606,"requestId":"F816:165513:16D7BF3:19868E9:6A052223"},"id":"050690b9-3cfa-4521-8c76-dd9c624d1f68","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:16:02.657Z","parentId":"5472cdc2-16dc-4265-a0f3-58fa5887610d"}
